WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.794
THERAPIST:
How are you both?

00:02.794 --> 00:04.463
DANNY: Great.
CLARE: Fine.

00:04.463 --> 00:05.422
Good.

00:05.839 --> 00:07.799
Danny blasted porn
on the Bluetooth speaker--

00:07.799 --> 00:10.511
Clare's vibrator literally
melted from overuse.

00:10.511 --> 00:11.887
♪

00:11.887 --> 00:13.347
CLARE:
<i>My life is a mess.</i>

00:13.347 --> 00:15.766
<i>My husband kicked me out
a few days ago.</i>

00:16.808 --> 00:18.727
<i>My daughter hates me.</i>
[gasps]

00:18.727 --> 00:20.312
- Oh, my God.
- Mom!

00:20.312 --> 00:21.772
A threesome is a big leap.

00:21.772 --> 00:25.192
Maybe you were subconsciously
worried about our little threesome?

00:25.192 --> 00:27.277
- What?
- Me and you and Dad.

00:27.277 --> 00:28.153
Ew!

00:28.153 --> 00:30.906
♪

00:30.906 --> 00:32.866
CLARE:
<i>What would I tell</i>

00:32.866 --> 00:35.744
<i>my 22-year-old self?</i>

00:35.744 --> 00:37.496
<i>Don't take your mom for granted.</i>

00:37.496 --> 00:39.540
<i>She won't be here forever.</i>

00:39.540 --> 00:41.500
♪

00:41.500 --> 00:43.877
<i>What does it mean to heal?
To move on?</i>

00:43.877 --> 00:46.088
<i>To let go?</i>

00:46.088 --> 00:48.632
♪

00:49.383 --> 00:51.718
Why can't you make new friends?
Like what happened to Bethany?

00:51.718 --> 00:54.096
Bethany had anal sex
on a Greyhound going to Reno.

00:54.096 --> 00:55.430
- What?
- Yeah.

00:55.430 --> 00:57.891
Why would she want to take
a bus to Reno?

01:01.144 --> 01:02.145
[keyboard clicking]

01:02.145 --> 01:03.438
WOMAN:
<i>Dear Sugar,</i>

01:04.231 --> 01:06.108
<i>I've never written a fan letter before,</i>

01:07.025 --> 01:09.862
<i>but I read your advice column religiously.</i>

01:11.238 --> 01:14.241
<i>Probably because
given the state of my life,</i>

01:14.241 --> 01:16.243
<i>I could use some advice.</i>

01:16.827 --> 01:19.246
<i>♪ Where they at? Where they at?
Where they at? Where they at? ♪</i>

01:19.246 --> 01:21.748
<i>♪ Where they at? Where they at?
Where they at? Come on now ♪</i>

01:21.748 --> 01:23.667
<i>♪ If you wanna go
and take a ride with me ♪</i>

01:23.667 --> 01:26.378
[woman singing along]
<i>♪ We three-wheeling
in the fo' with the gold D's ♪</i>

01:26.378 --> 01:29.131
<i>♪ Oh, why do I live this way? ♪</i>

01:29.131 --> 01:31.175
<i>♪ Hey, must be the money ♪</i>

01:31.175 --> 01:33.302
<i>♪ If you wanna go and get high with me ♪</i>

01:33.302 --> 01:35.137
<i>♪ Smoke an L
in the back of the Benz-E... ♪</i>

01:35.137 --> 01:38.557
[woman humming]

01:38.557 --> 01:40.475
<i>♪ Oh, must be the money ♪</i>

01:41.685 --> 01:43.645
WOMAN:
Which house is it again, dear?

01:47.399 --> 01:49.526
- Uh.
- Who can't find their way home?

01:49.526 --> 01:52.112
Oh, that's it.
That's the one, that's right there.

01:52.946 --> 01:55.908
Great job.
[continues singing]

01:55.908 --> 01:59.369
You know, thank you so much,
and happy retirement.

02:00.662 --> 02:01.747
Oh, it's locked.

02:02.372 --> 02:04.124
Sorry.
[locks click open]

02:04.666 --> 02:05.459
Thank you.

02:06.543 --> 02:07.794
Congratulations.

02:11.215 --> 02:13.383
Ooh, must be the money!

02:13.383 --> 02:14.259
Shhh.

02:15.802 --> 02:18.347
[car driving away]

02:22.518 --> 02:23.560
Noo.

02:33.987 --> 02:35.781
[knocks softly]

02:41.912 --> 02:42.913
Yes!

02:45.415 --> 02:46.416
[grunting]

02:48.877 --> 02:49.878
[bag thudding]

02:54.716 --> 02:58.679
[sing-song] Must be the money!
It's gotta be the money.

03:01.348 --> 03:03.559
[thuds]
[groans] Fuck!

03:06.603 --> 03:08.397
- [groaning]
- Don't you fucking move!

03:08.939 --> 03:11.358
Wha-- Oh, my God. Danny, it's just me.

03:11.358 --> 03:12.860
[footsteps thudding upstairs]
Shhh.

03:12.860 --> 03:15.988
Jesus, Clare! Shit, you had me--
I was about to call the cops!

03:15.988 --> 03:17.114
Why?

03:17.114 --> 03:19.324
What are you doing?
What are you wearing?

03:19.324 --> 03:23.620
Oh, I borrowed it.
It was, um... It's Hawaiian-themed.

03:23.620 --> 03:26.999
I didn't have my keys, and then I--

03:26.999 --> 03:30.460
The window was-- And it went so... late.

03:30.460 --> 03:31.503
You're drunk.

03:31.503 --> 03:34.173
Is there chicken?
'Cause it smells chickeney in here.

03:34.173 --> 03:36.258
Yeah, we had chicken. Six hours ago.

03:37.801 --> 03:38.802
Ugh.

03:41.597 --> 03:43.432
Mmm. Mm.

03:45.350 --> 03:46.560
Aah.

03:47.227 --> 03:48.312
Ah.

03:48.312 --> 03:50.063
There were toasts and speeches

03:50.063 --> 03:52.691
and, ugh, it's all so tragic, you know?

03:52.691 --> 03:56.987
It's like 43 years of work
just whittled down

03:56.987 --> 04:00.199
to a tray
of bacon-wrapped pineapple skewers

04:00.199 --> 04:03.410
and Retire-Mints. Get it?

04:03.410 --> 04:04.620
FRANKIE:
Mom?

04:04.620 --> 04:09.416
Oh, hey! Frankie, sweetie.

04:09.416 --> 04:13.629
- Rae.
- Hey, hon. You wan-- You want some mints?

04:13.629 --> 04:15.547
No. No one wants mints. Ever.

04:15.547 --> 04:16.715
[scoffs]

04:16.715 --> 04:18.342
So there's <i>no</i> chicken?

04:18.342 --> 04:19.801
We ate all the fucking chicken, Clare.

04:19.801 --> 04:20.761
Why are you here?

04:20.761 --> 04:22.679
Whoa! Okay.

04:23.263 --> 04:26.141
Why is everyone being such assholes?

04:26.141 --> 04:27.142
What's going on?

04:31.271 --> 04:32.648
Are you... back?

04:34.107 --> 04:36.026
Wha-- Huh?

04:37.861 --> 04:41.323
Well, I thought that you weren't
supposed to be here... or something.

04:46.662 --> 04:47.663
Oh.

04:50.624 --> 04:51.625
[moaning]

04:53.669 --> 04:55.003
Why am I eating this?

04:55.629 --> 04:57.548
Because you literally took the wheel
when we drove past--

04:57.548 --> 04:58.715
Well, you shouldn't have let me.

04:59.758 --> 05:00.843
Shouldn't have let me.

05:00.843 --> 05:02.427
You cannot tell Frankie.

05:02.427 --> 05:03.428
It's Rae.

05:03.929 --> 05:05.055
I hate calling her that.

05:06.557 --> 05:09.935
But she's right, though,
because they are horrible to gay people.

05:11.103 --> 05:12.312
Queer people. Sorry.

05:12.896 --> 05:14.690
But it isn't just their homophobia.

05:14.690 --> 05:18.235
It's-- it's-- Really, it's, like,
look here, it's all this crap

05:18.235 --> 05:21.113
that's just gonna
be floating on the planet forever.

05:21.113 --> 05:25.158
You know, wedged into the nostril
of some innocent turtle.

05:25.742 --> 05:27.995
But... [moans]

05:27.995 --> 05:29.913
...the butter and the pickles, it's just--

05:30.956 --> 05:31.915
Fucckk!

05:33.500 --> 05:35.878
- And those damn waffle fries.
- Ooh.

05:36.712 --> 05:37.796
So good.

05:37.796 --> 05:41.216
Well, it's what makes it all so hard.

05:43.385 --> 05:45.596
Everything good turns out to be bad.

05:46.346 --> 05:47.347
[chuckles]

06:01.195 --> 06:02.196
You're welcome.

06:05.407 --> 06:07.826
You kicked me out.
You want a "thank you"?

06:07.826 --> 06:09.661
You do realize you're not the victim?

06:09.661 --> 06:11.955
Well, neither are you, Danny.

06:11.955 --> 06:13.665
That's great.
CLARE: Neither are you!

06:13.665 --> 06:16.210
- All right. Absolutely great.
- Yeah, great, great. Thank you!

06:16.210 --> 06:17.377
[drink splashes]

06:26.512 --> 06:28.347
<i>My life is a mess, Sugar.</i>

06:29.139 --> 06:30.682
<i>My daughter hates me.</i>

06:30.682 --> 06:32.643
<i>My husband kicked me out a few nights ago,</i>

06:33.143 --> 06:36.188
<i>and he thinks
I'm crashing on my best friend's couch,</i>

06:36.188 --> 06:37.940
<i>but I'm not.</i>

06:37.940 --> 06:42.444
<i>I'm sitting on her stoop
waiting for an Uber... Pool.</i>

06:43.028 --> 06:46.031
♪

06:50.786 --> 06:54.039
<i>Wondering how the hell
my life ended up here,</i>

06:54.039 --> 06:57.835
<i>looking for comfort
from a woman I don't even know.</i>

06:57.835 --> 06:59.336
<i>And also wondering,</i>

06:59.336 --> 07:02.256
<i>has anyone ever written in
to offer comfort to you?</i>
[phone chimes]

07:05.425 --> 07:10.013
Then I told my mom,
"Bitch, college is for pussies.

07:10.013 --> 07:12.015
All that money to graduate for what?"

07:12.015 --> 07:14.476
[boy continues talking]
CLARE: <i>I read your response
in this week's column,</i>

07:14.476 --> 07:17.938
<i>and one sentence
buried deep within your advice</i>

07:17.938 --> 07:19.940
<i>compelled me to write.</i>

07:19.940 --> 07:23.277
<i>It was a sentence
about your sister and her cancer.</i>

07:26.738 --> 07:28.991
<i>I'm sorry
that she died too young and too soon.</i>

07:30.492 --> 07:31.952
Oh, wait. This is good.

07:31.952 --> 07:33.245
Wait. Stop, stop, stop.

07:36.665 --> 07:37.583
PASSENGER:
Cool pad.

07:39.334 --> 07:40.294
[device beeps]

07:40.294 --> 07:42.171
CLARE:
<i>But that's the thing about grief,</i>

07:43.005 --> 07:45.924
<i>you can't cry it away or eat it away</i>

07:45.924 --> 07:47.384
<i>or punch it away.</i>

07:48.635 --> 07:50.554
<i>It's just... there,</i>

07:51.471 --> 07:53.265
<i>and you have to survive it.</i>

07:53.265 --> 07:55.184
<i>You have to endure it.</i>

07:55.184 --> 07:56.643
<i>You have to live with it,</i>

07:58.145 --> 07:59.897
<i>which is the hardest thing in the world.</i>

08:04.735 --> 08:06.778
<i>I was 22 when my mother was diagnosed.</i>

08:09.323 --> 08:10.699
WOMAN:
<i>Everyone, ready?</i>

08:10.699 --> 08:12.159
Yes.
BOY: Yes.

08:12.784 --> 08:16.246
Clare Marie Pierce
is an award-winning essay writer

08:16.246 --> 08:19.124
and soon-to-be college graduate
with a 4.0,

08:19.124 --> 08:22.836
who is committed to summiting
Machu Picchu over spring break!
- Mexico!

08:22.836 --> 08:24.505
Come on out, Clare!

08:24.505 --> 08:27.508
[both cheering]

08:29.009 --> 08:31.470
And now, a high school senior

08:31.470 --> 08:33.514
who cannot get a tattoo
until he graduates,

08:33.514 --> 08:35.182
no matter how compelling his argument,

08:35.182 --> 08:38.018
- and who's--
- Is still a virgin!

08:38.018 --> 08:39.019
BOY:
Stop saying that.

08:39.019 --> 08:40.604
Worn the same T-shirt
for four days running

08:40.604 --> 08:43.982
and appears to have
no intention of taking it off!

08:44.525 --> 08:48.403
- Get out here, Lucas!
- Lucas!

08:48.403 --> 08:51.657
[both cheering]

08:51.657 --> 08:52.866
Yeah.

08:52.866 --> 08:54.409
Are we ever gonna be too old for this?

08:54.409 --> 08:55.744
We'll be doing this when I'm 80.

08:57.287 --> 08:58.413
Merry Christmas.

08:59.081 --> 09:01.667
CLARE: <i>And lately,
I keep playing our last Christmas together</i>

09:01.667 --> 09:04.086
<i>over and over in my mind.</i>

09:05.838 --> 09:07.297
WOMAN:
<i>Me first.</i>

09:07.297 --> 09:09.091
Me first.

09:09.925 --> 09:11.343
I get to go first.

09:15.013 --> 09:16.014
Ooh.

09:16.974 --> 09:20.435
LUCAS: Oh, no way!
Is it vintage or something?

09:20.435 --> 09:22.020
I knew you wanted one.

09:22.813 --> 09:24.064
It was your father's.

09:26.441 --> 09:27.442
He sent it?

09:29.152 --> 09:30.529
I refurbished it.

09:32.322 --> 09:34.408
- [tool clatters]
- Lucas, don't be a little shit.

09:34.408 --> 09:35.868
Somebody gives you something, you take it.

09:35.868 --> 09:36.869
You take it.

09:36.869 --> 09:38.662
I'm not the one
who's ever wanted anything from him.

09:38.662 --> 09:40.664
It's okay. He doesn't have to.

09:44.126 --> 09:46.003
All right, you go ahead, honey.

09:48.213 --> 09:49.798
Jess said that you needed one.

09:49.798 --> 09:51.800
And I thought
that it would be great for New York.

10:01.602 --> 10:02.603
Do you like it?

10:03.687 --> 10:04.688
Yeah, I love it.

10:07.274 --> 10:08.942
Uh-- I do. I-- I love it.

10:08.942 --> 10:10.652
[mockingly] You do? You love it?

10:11.153 --> 10:12.154
Hey.

10:15.866 --> 10:16.867
Uh, it's--

10:17.951 --> 10:18.952
It's long

10:19.578 --> 10:22.247
and subs-- substantial.

10:22.581 --> 10:23.582
I thought it was unique.

10:28.670 --> 10:29.671
I just wonder, does it--

10:31.256 --> 10:32.841
Does it make more sense to get black?

10:33.342 --> 10:37.012
Because it's dirty in New York,
and it'll probably last longer.

10:37.012 --> 10:38.764
And it's-- it's probably easy to exchange.

10:40.599 --> 10:43.977
Sure. Sure.
You should have what you want, honey.

10:47.272 --> 10:49.691
CLARE:
<i>I hope, in your sister's death,</i>

10:49.691 --> 10:52.361
<i>you'll be able
to do something that I haven't.</i>

10:52.361 --> 10:54.112
<i>Create something of her life.</i>

10:55.614 --> 10:56.782
<i>Make it beautiful.</i>

10:57.991 --> 11:00.410
<i>And then, please, tell me how you did it.</i>

11:01.995 --> 11:04.081
<i>Love, Clare.</i>

11:05.374 --> 11:08.377
♪

11:39.783 --> 11:40.993
Uh, that can come down.

11:42.160 --> 11:45.998
You were so wasted last night.
How are you even walking this morning?

11:45.998 --> 11:47.291
CLARE:
I don't know, Shan.

11:47.291 --> 11:48.667
Somehow I stagger on,

11:48.667 --> 11:52.171
despite fielding the vitriol
of an entitled millennial.

11:52.171 --> 11:54.631
SHAN:
I mean, <i>literally</i> walking.

11:54.631 --> 11:56.550
When you fell off the stage
after "Me and Bobby McGee,"

11:56.550 --> 11:59.761
I thought you, like,
broke a hip... or something.

12:02.931 --> 12:05.392
Would you just take
the fucking sign down, Shan? Thank you.

12:06.560 --> 12:09.730
Oh, Bev's daughter wanted you
to come by. Room 19.

12:09.730 --> 12:11.064
She told me it was urgent.

12:15.360 --> 12:17.946
- When?
- Like, an hour ago.

12:18.447 --> 12:19.448
[Clare scoffs]

12:21.450 --> 12:23.202
[Clare mumbling]

12:23.202 --> 12:24.578
SHAN:
And I'm a Zoomer.

12:27.289 --> 12:29.208
CLARE:
Krystal, I'm so sorry to keep you waiting.

12:29.208 --> 12:30.292
I just got your message.

12:30.292 --> 12:32.127
- Did you sleep in here last night?
- Uh...

12:32.127 --> 12:34.796
My mom said
the admissions lady slept here last night.

12:39.676 --> 12:42.638
I know that you get lonely sometimes.

12:42.638 --> 12:46.350
And even though
you know that I can't sleep in here,

12:46.350 --> 12:48.018
I will always keep you company

12:48.018 --> 12:51.647
and make sure you're feeling cozy
and all tucked in, right?

12:51.647 --> 12:52.940
- Right?
- Mmm.

12:54.149 --> 12:55.442
[whispering] It's the Alzheimer's.

12:59.613 --> 13:00.948
- There you go.
- Thank you.

13:01.448 --> 13:02.533
Gentleman.

13:05.661 --> 13:07.371
- What?
- Wow.

13:07.371 --> 13:09.122
CLARE:
Oh, my God!

13:09.122 --> 13:11.667
Sam! What're you doing here?

13:11.667 --> 13:14.670
SAM: Oh, it's been--
CLARE: Been forever! Shit!

13:14.670 --> 13:16.922
- You look great!
- Wha-- Oh.

13:16.922 --> 13:19.258
- Wait, when was the last time--
- I don't know!

13:19.258 --> 13:20.926
Was it, uh, Bread Loaf?

13:20.926 --> 13:22.886
Uh, uh, City Lights. Hannah's reading.

13:22.886 --> 13:24.388
Oh, fuck! Yeah.

13:25.305 --> 13:28.392
Aah. Wait, are you still at,
uh, uh, <i>The Believer?</i>

13:28.392 --> 13:30.102
No. They folded in March.

13:30.102 --> 13:32.354
But I left for <i>The Mantros</i> years ago.

13:32.354 --> 13:34.815
Oh, I love <i>The Mantros.</i>

13:34.815 --> 13:37.317
Essays... Dear Sugar...

13:37.317 --> 13:39.444
I know!
I got your fan letter last night!

13:42.489 --> 13:43.699
You wrote in to Dear Sugar.

13:45.951 --> 13:46.952
I'm Sugar.

13:48.871 --> 13:50.956
I'll explain. Do you want to go somewhere?

13:50.956 --> 13:51.957
Do you still not drive?

13:53.166 --> 13:55.669
An advice column is easy clicks.

13:55.669 --> 13:59.423
But who-- who wants to get advice
from some middle-aged white dude?

13:59.423 --> 14:02.342
I've literally been reading this column
for the last three months,

14:02.342 --> 14:03.635
and it's fucking <i>you?</i>

14:03.635 --> 14:05.804
- How can it be <i>you?</i>
- I'm detecting some disdain here.

14:05.804 --> 14:09.099
You're pretending
to be a-- a <i>woman?</i> What?

14:09.099 --> 14:11.268
I know. I know! I am living a lie.

14:11.268 --> 14:14.104
But then... you wrote in.

14:14.104 --> 14:16.690
And I saw your name
and I remembered your writing

14:16.690 --> 14:18.901
and the essay--
That <i>fucking</i> essay.

14:19.318 --> 14:23.071
And I realized that this woman
that I'm pretending to be,

14:23.071 --> 14:26.742
you know, working class,
pulled herself up by her bootstraps,

14:26.742 --> 14:28.160
- kinda disheveled--
- Okay.

14:28.160 --> 14:29.620
- She's <i>literally</i> you!
- Okay. Okay.

14:29.620 --> 14:32.497
- Okay, just take a left at Elm.
- <i>You</i> should be the one doing this.

14:33.081 --> 14:34.166
Doing what?

14:34.166 --> 14:36.710
- Being Sugar!
- What? No.

14:36.710 --> 14:37.711
I mean, it doesn't pay.

14:37.711 --> 14:41.089
And-- And, you know,
there's no credit 'cause it's anonymous.

14:41.089 --> 14:42.841
But I would be your point.

14:42.841 --> 14:46.470
And all you have to do
is answer, like, one letter a week and--

14:46.470 --> 14:47.971
Sam, stop it.

14:47.971 --> 14:50.015
I'm not giving anybody advice.

14:50.015 --> 14:54.019
My life is a fucking shit show!

14:55.646 --> 14:56.772
And I--

14:56.772 --> 14:58.357
I'm not a writer!

14:58.357 --> 15:00.651
You're one of the best writers I know.

15:01.527 --> 15:05.322
You didn't get a book deal
off of that essay for nothing.

15:05.322 --> 15:07.950
Doesn't count
if you don't write the book.

15:07.950 --> 15:09.952
Everything counts, Sugar.

15:12.287 --> 15:13.455
Don't call me that!

15:22.589 --> 15:24.174
I'm sorry about your sister.

15:26.677 --> 15:29.763
Clare, I don't have a fucking sister.
I made it up.

15:29.763 --> 15:33.559
You made up someone
having fucking <i>cancer?</i>

15:33.559 --> 15:35.060
Take a right.

15:35.060 --> 15:37.104
SAM:
Yes, I made it all up!

15:37.104 --> 15:38.397
This is why I need you!

15:38.397 --> 15:40.357
Oh, you are the worst, Sam!

15:40.357 --> 15:42.192
I can't believe
I almost ever slept with you.

15:42.192 --> 15:43.193
Pull over!

15:43.193 --> 15:45.195
SAM: What are you doing?
CLARE: I'm-- I'm getting out.

15:45.195 --> 15:46.530
Wait, what do you mean, "almost"?

15:46.530 --> 15:48.282
We never slept together? Why not?

15:48.282 --> 15:50.158
'Cause you're an asshole.

15:50.158 --> 15:53.078
Oh, so you're done with me now?
That's it?

15:53.078 --> 15:55.622
I have therapy. Thank you for the ride.

15:55.622 --> 15:58.458
- What? <i>You're</i> an asshole!
- Okay, fine.

15:58.458 --> 16:00.169
SAM:
No, no, no, no. Here. Wait.

16:00.169 --> 16:03.547
I-- I printed out
the letters that I didn't answer

16:03.547 --> 16:05.007
because I can't-- [mumbles]

16:05.716 --> 16:09.428
Just... read 'em.
And if you want, just answer one.

16:11.013 --> 16:14.266
Everyone's lives are a <i>fucking</i> shit show!

16:14.266 --> 16:16.310
People, they need help.

16:16.310 --> 16:20.022
You said it yourself,
"Create something of her life.
Make it beautiful."

16:23.358 --> 16:24.943
EMPLOYEE:
Let me see if I can help you.

16:24.943 --> 16:26.486
Did you happen to save the receipt?

16:26.486 --> 16:29.323
I... did not save the receipt.

16:29.323 --> 16:31.033
It was final sale.

16:31.033 --> 16:33.202
EMPLOYEE:
I-- I can try to look it up.

16:33.702 --> 16:34.995
WOMAN:
I appreciate that.

16:37.623 --> 16:39.416
EMPLOYEE:
I may need to talk to my supervisor.

16:45.964 --> 16:48.008
- Did it work out?
- Mm-hmm.

16:48.008 --> 16:49.259
- It's okay?
- It's okay.

16:55.432 --> 16:56.433
You're late.

16:56.433 --> 16:57.893
I'm actually two minutes early

16:57.893 --> 17:00.729
'cause she's always
five minutes late, so.

17:00.729 --> 17:03.398
[phone dings]
CLARE: [softly] Make sure that's off.

17:06.860 --> 17:08.070
Who is it?

17:09.154 --> 17:10.739
Hmm?
DANNY: [scoffs] Lucas again?

17:13.992 --> 17:16.411
WOMAN: I'm glad
you both are choosing to be here today.

17:18.830 --> 17:21.041
I know, in the past,
that hasn't always been the case.

17:23.627 --> 17:26.421
This feels like a particularly hard moment
in your marriage.

17:27.381 --> 17:29.383
I think a <i>lot</i> has been said.

17:30.551 --> 17:33.971
And maybe... a lot <i>hasn't</i> been said.

17:37.099 --> 17:39.893
Yeah. No, um, I-- I feel that same way.

17:40.727 --> 17:42.729
Honestly, it's, um...

17:44.231 --> 17:45.232
Uh...

17:47.693 --> 17:48.694
Yeah.

17:50.445 --> 17:53.949
Jung once said,
"I am not what has happened to me.

17:54.741 --> 17:56.869
I am what I choose to become."

17:57.536 --> 17:59.288
Does that bring up
anything for you, Clare?

17:59.288 --> 18:00.289
No.

18:00.914 --> 18:04.042
How long am I supposed
to stay out of my own home?

18:04.042 --> 18:06.420
Well, how long do you think
you need to stay out of your home?

18:09.089 --> 18:10.549
What are we doing?

18:10.549 --> 18:14.136
What is this <i>space</i> supposed to accomplish?

18:14.136 --> 18:18.015
Or is it just, like,
one long, torturous experiment

18:18.015 --> 18:20.726
to slowly turn my own daughter against me?

18:20.726 --> 18:21.977
It was her college fund!

18:21.977 --> 18:23.854
Part of. That he will pay back!

18:23.854 --> 18:25.856
You just gave it away
without even talking to me!

18:25.856 --> 18:27.524
What? You just thought I wouldn't notice?

18:27.524 --> 18:29.818
What did you want me to fucking do?
Leave him homeless?

18:29.818 --> 18:32.821
It was our childhood home!
It's my mother's house!

18:32.821 --> 18:35.324
He lives there! And it was underwater.

18:35.324 --> 18:37.034
Yeah, because he fucked up.

18:37.034 --> 18:38.160
Yeah, he fucks up all the time!

18:38.160 --> 18:39.494
Yeah, he does fuck up all the time and--

18:39.494 --> 18:41.997
Yeah, fine, fine!
But family takes care of family.

18:42.497 --> 18:43.665
I'm it for him.

18:43.665 --> 18:45.918
What would you do?
Would you leave me on the fucking street?

18:46.668 --> 18:48.420
Oh! [scoffs]

18:48.420 --> 18:52.216
Clare, have you ever heard
of the phrase "financial infidelity"?

18:52.216 --> 18:53.217
Oh, my God.

18:53.217 --> 18:57.095
It can be as destabilizing
and damaging as sexual infidelity.

18:57.095 --> 18:58.096
Even more so.

18:58.096 --> 18:59.097
Yeah. Okay.

18:59.097 --> 19:00.974
That's not even in the same ballpark,

19:00.974 --> 19:02.809
- 'cause there's no betrayal here.
- Right.

19:02.809 --> 19:04.728
I needed to take care of my brother.

19:04.728 --> 19:07.022
Yeah, when you do something wrong,
it's-- it's different rules.

19:07.022 --> 19:08.315
This is not about rules.

19:08.315 --> 19:10.317
Not everybody comes from
where you come from,

19:10.317 --> 19:13.862
or just-- or, you know,
starts life with an even playing field.

19:13.862 --> 19:15.113
I'm a Black man in America.

19:15.113 --> 19:17.241
I know people don't come
from an equal playing field, Clare.

19:17.241 --> 19:19.326
That's not what I mean.
I'm talking about being rich!

19:19.326 --> 19:21.245
- I grew up middle class.
- Yeah, that's rich.

19:21.245 --> 19:24.164
What do you want me to say?
My brother's a fuck-up. I'm a fuck-up.

19:24.164 --> 19:25.332
Okay, I'm an awful person.

19:25.332 --> 19:27.167
I'm awful. I'm horrible. That's it.

19:27.167 --> 19:29.211
I don't know what to say.
I don't know what to fucking say.

19:29.878 --> 19:31.630
Let's just start
with how you're feeling, hm?

19:31.630 --> 19:35.551
I am feeling hungry. I am feeling tired.

19:35.551 --> 19:37.845
I'm feeling like a shell of a person.

19:37.845 --> 19:40.681
- Like I'm staring into an abyss--
- I get it.

19:43.058 --> 19:44.643
I mean, I'm not there yet,

19:44.643 --> 19:48.021
but I think it's really common
for women your age to feel this way.

19:48.021 --> 19:49.314
You've spoken before

19:49.314 --> 19:51.525
about your insecurities
with getting older--

19:51.525 --> 19:53.777
I thought we were talking
about me giving money to my brother.

19:53.777 --> 19:56.572
- And with the age gap
between you and Danny--
- It's not that big.

19:56.572 --> 19:59.992
And the way our society
treats women over 50 as irrelevant--

19:59.992 --> 20:01.702
- I'm 49!
- You'll be 50 in a month.

20:01.702 --> 20:05.247
Women over 50 are treated
as if they are barely sexual beings.

20:05.247 --> 20:09.751
Their beauty is fading, or at least
our conventional ideas of beauty.

20:09.751 --> 20:11.712
Because of that, their power wanes.

20:11.712 --> 20:15.966
Their wants and desires
are considered as an afterthought.

20:16.800 --> 20:17.801
Okay.

20:22.598 --> 20:23.599
[keys jingle]

20:41.408 --> 20:42.409
Oh.

20:48.248 --> 20:50.250
[muffled conversation]

21:00.093 --> 21:02.679
[Danny speaking indistinctly]

21:02.679 --> 21:04.681
♪

21:08.685 --> 21:10.103
I mean, it's therapy!

21:10.103 --> 21:13.398
It's not office hours.
You don't stick around after class!

21:13.398 --> 21:17.069
You know, that's like a cesspool
full of bacteria, right?

21:17.069 --> 21:20.155
Okay, why don't you ask
your hot dishwasher to clean it out?

21:20.781 --> 21:23.075
Oh, well, maybe I will.

21:24.701 --> 21:25.744
- Hello.
- There you go.

21:25.744 --> 21:26.828
Oh, my God!

21:26.828 --> 21:27.829
WOMAN:
Thank you.

21:27.829 --> 21:29.498
[woman laughing]

21:29.498 --> 21:30.791
Jesus Christ, Amy!

21:30.791 --> 21:32.793
[Amy snickering]

21:33.293 --> 21:34.795
I'm naughty!

21:34.795 --> 21:36.630
Uh, are they having sex?

21:36.630 --> 21:38.215
They-- Do they wanna have sex?

21:38.924 --> 21:43.470
Is couple's therapy some,
you know, sick psycho foreplay

21:43.470 --> 21:47.349
where they're just telepathically
jerking each other off in front of me?

21:47.349 --> 21:50.853
And... is my insurance paying for it?

21:50.853 --> 21:53.897
Oh, my God!
Maybe I should be a couple's therapist.

21:53.897 --> 21:55.607
CLARE:
I mean, I'm the one who found her!

21:55.607 --> 21:58.110
He didn't even wanna go!
And now he's like, what-- He's what?

21:58.110 --> 22:00.362
He's, like, fucking some woman

22:00.362 --> 22:05.409
who decorates her office with gnomes
grabbing their own weird stone vaginas?

22:05.409 --> 22:07.619
Okay. Danny loves you.

22:07.619 --> 22:12.249
He's not fucking his therapist
or any stone, uh, vaginas, okay?

22:13.792 --> 22:16.086
She called me barely a woman.

22:18.964 --> 22:20.591
Am I barely a woman?

22:20.591 --> 22:22.509
I mean,
she probably said it to get laid.

22:22.509 --> 22:25.220
Thanks, Amy.
AMY: Hang in there.

22:33.520 --> 22:34.521
Thanks.

22:48.660 --> 22:49.661
Hey.

22:51.038 --> 22:52.039
Hey.

22:56.168 --> 22:58.170
♪

23:03.967 --> 23:04.968
[softly] Hey.

23:06.178 --> 23:09.181
♪

23:20.984 --> 23:24.321
[young Clare moaning]

23:35.541 --> 23:37.751
[Clare grunting] Okay.

23:37.751 --> 23:39.044
MAN:
I can't get it in.

23:39.044 --> 23:41.463
No, it's because, uh--
It's-- it's-- The angle is wrong

23:42.673 --> 23:43.799
Okay, yeah, maybe we--

23:43.799 --> 23:44.925
- Yeah.
- Yeah, let's go.

23:45.801 --> 23:46.927
[squishing]

23:46.927 --> 23:49.304
What the f--
Wait, what the fuck is happening?

23:49.888 --> 23:51.640
Wait, is this a waterbed?

23:51.640 --> 23:53.892
Oh, my God!
[laughing] Oh, my God.

23:53.892 --> 23:56.228
Am I in 1979?

23:56.228 --> 24:00.232
Am I in a-- Am I trapped
in a fucking Steely Dan song?

24:00.232 --> 24:02.192
Oh, my God.

24:03.068 --> 24:05.487
- Oh, my God. Oh, my God.
- What?

24:05.487 --> 24:09.241
[Clare laughing and crying]

24:10.492 --> 24:12.870
- Oh, my God.
- Are you okay?

24:12.870 --> 24:15.747
[Clare crying]

24:15.747 --> 24:18.625
I am not okay.

24:20.252 --> 24:21.461
Wait, are you married?

24:22.129 --> 24:24.590
- What the--
- The ring on your finger?

24:25.507 --> 24:28.677
Are you gonna fucking judge me?
You have a fucking waterbed!

24:28.677 --> 24:29.678
So?

24:34.391 --> 24:36.143
And I like Steely Dan.

24:37.227 --> 24:38.854
Well, they're a great band.

24:49.740 --> 24:51.325
[phone chimes]

25:04.963 --> 25:07.966
♪

25:27.319 --> 25:28.695
WOMAN:
<i>Dear Sugar,</i>

25:28.695 --> 25:30.989
<i>I'm 22, and my question is short.</i>

25:32.032 --> 25:33.867
<i>What would you tell
your 20-something self</i>

25:33.867 --> 25:35.244
<i>if you could talk to her now?</i>

25:36.328 --> 25:38.205
<i>Love, Seeking Wisdom.</i>

25:40.415 --> 25:43.418
♪

25:45.629 --> 25:46.672
CLARE:

25:50.634 --> 25:51.635
<i>Dear...</i>

25:56.265 --> 25:58.058
<i>Dear Seeking Wisdom.</i>

25:59.142 --> 26:01.937
<i>What would I tell my 22-year-old self?</i>

26:03.480 --> 26:05.816
<i>I'd say,
stop worrying whether you're fat.</i>

26:06.525 --> 26:08.360
<i>Feed yourself, literally.</i>

26:09.528 --> 26:13.699
<i>The people worthy of your love
will love you more for this.</i>

26:18.495 --> 26:23.292
<i>I'd also say that
most things will be okay eventually,</i>

26:24.835 --> 26:26.086
<i>but not everything.</i>

26:31.842 --> 26:33.802
<i>One afternoon in your 20s,</i>

26:33.802 --> 26:37.139
<i>when you've gotten yourself
ridiculously tangled up with heroin,</i>

26:37.139 --> 26:40.934
<i>you'll be riding the bus and thinking
what a worthless piece of shit you are.</i>

26:42.352 --> 26:44.730
<i>A little girl will get on the bus
with her mother,</i>

26:44.730 --> 26:46.815
<i>holding the strings
of two purple balloons.</i>

26:47.566 --> 26:50.569
<i>She will offer you one of the balloons,
but you won't take it</i>

26:50.569 --> 26:52.946
<i>because you believe
you no longer have a right</i>

26:52.946 --> 26:55.199
<i>to such tiny beautiful things.</i>

27:00.037 --> 27:01.038
<i>You're wrong.</i>

27:04.124 --> 27:05.125
<i>You do.</i>

27:07.419 --> 27:12.049
EMPLOYEE:
That's $127.62. I'm so sorry.

27:12.049 --> 27:14.635
CLARE: <i>And someday,
you'll look back on that one Christmas,</i>

27:14.635 --> 27:16.970
<i>when your mother gave you
a mustard-yellow coat</i>

27:16.970 --> 27:19.139
<i>that she'd saved for months to buy.</i>

27:21.225 --> 27:24.228
♪

27:27.814 --> 27:28.899
<i>Don't hold it up and say</i>

27:28.899 --> 27:30.692
<i>it's longer than
you like your coats to be,</i>

27:30.692 --> 27:34.571
<i>and too puffy,
and possibly even too warm.</i>

27:36.532 --> 27:38.867
<i>Because your mother
will be dead by spring...</i>

27:38.867 --> 27:39.868
[door opens]

27:41.036 --> 27:43.455
<i>...and that coat will be the last gift
she ever gave you.</i>

27:44.831 --> 27:45.832
Are you okay?

27:50.420 --> 27:51.797
I love you. [sniffles]

27:53.298 --> 27:54.800
You know that, right?

27:54.800 --> 27:57.302
Ab-- About the money,
it's-- it's not gone.

27:57.302 --> 27:58.846
It's not about the money.

27:58.846 --> 27:59.847
Then what?

28:04.142 --> 28:05.435
Do you want me to bring that in?

28:11.650 --> 28:13.819
CLARE: <i>And you will regret
the small thing you didn't say</i>

28:13.819 --> 28:14.945
<i>for the rest of your life.</i>

28:15.863 --> 28:16.864
RAE:
Have a good night.

28:19.157 --> 28:20.158
You too.

28:20.158 --> 28:23.704
<i>When a gift is given, say thank you.</i>

28:23.704 --> 28:24.705
Mom?

28:30.836 --> 28:31.837
You dropped something.

28:33.213 --> 28:37.467
CLARE:
<i>When a gift is given, say thank you.</i>

28:44.183 --> 28:46.727
<i>When a gift... is given...</i>

28:49.521 --> 28:50.772
[door closes]

28:50.772 --> 28:51.773
Thank you.

28:56.945 --> 28:59.948
♪

29:01.408 --> 29:05.120
<i>♪ I'm trying to tell you
something 'bout my life ♪</i>

29:06.663 --> 29:11.126
<i>♪ Maybe give me insight
between black and white ♪</i>

29:11.126 --> 29:14.880
<i>♪ And the best thing
that you ever done for me ♪</i>

29:16.131 --> 29:19.885
<i>♪ Is to help me
take my life less seriously ♪</i>

29:19.885 --> 29:22.638
<i>♪ It's only life after all ♪</i>

29:26.016 --> 29:28.477
<i>♪ I went to the doctor ♪</i>

29:28.477 --> 29:30.896
<i>♪ I went to the mountains ♪</i>

29:30.896 --> 29:33.357
<i>♪ I looked to the children ♪</i>

29:33.357 --> 29:35.817
<i>♪ I drank from the fountains ♪</i>

29:35.817 --> 29:39.571
<i>♪ There's more than one answer
to these questions ♪</i>

29:39.571 --> 29:42.157
<i>♪ Pointing me in a crooked line ♪</i>

29:43.075 --> 29:46.870
<i>♪ And the less I seek my source ♪</i>

29:46.870 --> 29:51.124
<i>♪ The closer I am to fine ♪</i>

29:52.084 --> 30:01.969
<i>♪ Closer I am to fine ♪</i>
